---
import Callout from "../../components/Callout.astro";
import Step from "../../components/Step.astro";
import TroubleshootItem from "../../components/TroubleshootItem.astro";
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="Amazon Polly setup · Cloud Speech for Chrome"
  description="Step-by-step Amazon Polly setup for the Cloud Speech Chrome extension: create an AWS account, an IAM user, access keys, and connect the extension."
  root="../../"
  active="polly"
>
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-12">
    <p>
      <a class="link text-sm text-stone-600" href="../../#guides">← Back to all guides</a>
    </p>

    <header class="mt-8">
      <p
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full bg-polly/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-stone-700"
      >
        <span class="h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-polly"></span>
        Setup guide
      </p>
      <h1 class="mt-4 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">Set up Amazon Polly</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-stone-600">
        Amazon Polly is AWS's text-to-speech service, with hundreds of voices across Standard,
        Neural, Generative, and Long-form engines. This guide walks you through creating AWS
        credentials from scratch. No developer experience needed. It takes about 10 minutes.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="card mt-8 p-5">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold">What you'll need</h2>
      <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-sm leading-relaxed text-stone-600">
        <li>An AWS account (free tier available; a payment method is required to sign up)</li>
        <li>About 10 minutes</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <ol
      class="relative mt-12 space-y-12 before:absolute before:top-2 before:bottom-2 before:left-4 before:w-px before:bg-stone-200"
    >
      <Step n={1} title="Create an AWS account">
        <p>If you don't have an AWS account yet:</p>
        <ol class="list-decimal space-y-1.5 pl-5 marker:text-stone-400">
          <li>Go to <a class="link" href="https://aws.amazon.com">aws.amazon.com</a></li>
          <li>Click <strong>Create an AWS Account</strong></li>
          <li>Follow the registration process</li>
          <li>
            Add a payment method (the free tier covers basic usage; see the costs box below)
          </li>
        </ol>
        <p class="text-stone-500">Already have an AWS account? Skip straight to step 2.</p>
      </Step>

      <Step n={2} title="Create an IAM user with Polly access">
        <p>
          For security, create a dedicated user that can <em>only</em> use Polly. Never use your
          root account credentials in the extension:
        </p>
        <ol class="list-decimal space-y-1.5 pl-5 marker:text-stone-400">
          <li>
            Sign in to the
            <a class="link" href="https://console.aws.amazon.com">AWS Console</a>
          </li>
          <li>Search for and open the <strong>IAM</strong> service</li>
          <li>Click <strong>Users → Create user</strong></li>
          <li>Enter a username, e.g. <span class="value">cloud-speech-extension</span></li>
          <li>Select <strong>Attach policies directly</strong></li>
          <li>Search for and select <span class="value">AmazonPollyReadOnlyAccess</span></li>
          <li>Click <strong>Create user</strong></li>
        </ol>
      </Step>

      <Step n={3} title="Generate access keys">
        <p>Create the keys the extension will use to talk to Polly:</p>
        <ol class="list-decimal space-y-1.5 pl-5 marker:text-stone-400">
          <li>Click on your newly created user</li>
          <li>Open the <strong>Security credentials</strong> tab</li>
          <li>Click <strong>Create access key</strong></li>
          <li>Select <strong>Application running outside AWS</strong></li>
          <li>
            Add a description, e.g. <span class="value">Cloud Speech Chrome extension</span>
          </li>
          <li>Click <strong>Create access key</strong></li>
          <li>
            Copy <strong>both</strong> the <strong>Access Key ID</strong> and the
            <strong>Secret Access Key</strong>
          </li>
        </ol>
        <Callout title="Security warning">
          Save your Secret Access Key immediately, because AWS will never show it again. Keep these
          credentials secure and never share them.
        </Callout>
      </Step>

      <Step n={4} title="Choose your region">
        <p>Select the AWS region closest to you for better performance. Popular choices:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-1.5 pl-5 marker:text-stone-400">
          <li><span class="value">us-east-1</span> — N. Virginia (cheapest)</li>
          <li><span class="value">us-west-2</span> — Oregon</li>
          <li><span class="value">eu-west-1</span> — Ireland</li>
          <li><span class="value">ap-southeast-1</span> — Singapore</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          See the
          <a class="link" href="https://docs.aws.amazon.com/general/latest/gr/pol.html"
            >AWS Polly regions list</a
          >
          for all options. Note that not every engine (e.g. Generative) is available in every
          region.
        </p>
      </Step>

      <Step n={5} title="Connect the extension">
        <ol class="list-decimal space-y-1.5 pl-5 marker:text-stone-400">
          <li>Click the extension icon in your browser toolbar</li>
          <li>Open <strong>Settings → Amazon Polly</strong></li>
          <li>Paste your <strong>Access Key ID</strong></li>
          <li>Paste your <strong>Secret Access Key</strong></li>
          <li>
            Enter your chosen <strong>Region</strong> (e.g. <span class="value">us-east-1</span>)
          </li>
          <li>Click <strong>Save &amp; test</strong></li>
        </ol>
        <p>
          Once the test passes, the Polly voices appear in the voice picker. Press ▶ to preview
          any voice and ★ to favorite the ones you like. Then highlight text on any page,
          right-click, and choose <em>Read aloud</em>, or press <kbd>Ctrl/Cmd+Shift+S</kbd>.
        </p>
      </Step>
    </ol>

    <!-- Costs -->
    <section class="card mt-12 p-6">
      <h2 class="flex items-center gap-2.5 text-lg font-semibold">
        <span class="h-2.5 w-2.5 rounded-full bg-polly"></span>
        Costs
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-stone-700">
        AWS's free tier includes <strong>5 million characters per month</strong> for standard
        voices and <strong>1 million characters per month</strong> for neural voices during your
        first 12 months. After that (or beyond the free tier):
      </p>
      <ul
        class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-1.5 pl-5 text-sm leading-relaxed text-stone-700 marker:text-stone-400"
      >
        <li><strong>Standard voices:</strong> $4.00 per 1 million characters</li>
        <li><strong>Neural voices:</strong> $16.00 per 1 million characters</li>
        <li><strong>Generative voices:</strong> $30.00 per 1 million characters</li>
        <li><strong>Long-form voices:</strong> $100.00 per 1 million characters</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-stone-700">
        Every character, including spaces, counts. See the
        <a class="link" href="https://aws.amazon.com/polly/pricing/"
          >official Polly pricing page</a
        >
        and our <a class="link" href="../../pricing/">provider comparison</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Troubleshooting -->
    <section class="mt-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Troubleshooting</h2>
      <div class="card mt-4 divide-y divide-stone-100">
        <TroubleshootItem title='"Credentials are missing or invalid"'>
          <p>
            Double-check the values you pasted; a stray space or missing character is the most
            common cause. Ensure your IAM user has the
            <span class="value">AmazonPollyReadOnlyAccess</span> policy, your region is correct
            (e.g. <span class="value">us-east-1</span>), and the access keys are still active in
            the AWS Console. Then click <strong>Save &amp; test</strong> again.
          </p>
        </TroubleshootItem>
        <TroubleshootItem title='"Access denied" errors'>
          <p>
            Your credentials are valid but lack permission. Attach
            <span class="value">AmazonPollyReadOnlyAccess</span>, and check that the engine you
            picked (e.g. Generative) is available in your selected region.
          </p>
        </TroubleshootItem>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-stone-600">
        For no audio, missing voices, or keyboard shortcut problems, see the
        <a class="link" href="../../troubleshooting/">troubleshooting guide</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <p class="mt-10 text-sm leading-relaxed text-stone-600">
      Prefer a different provider? See
      <a class="link" href="../azure/">Azure Speech</a>,
      <a class="link" href="../google/">Google Cloud TTS</a>, or
      <a class="link" href="../openai/">OpenAI</a>.
    </p>
  </main>
</Base>
